Pour the @water for the rice{} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling,
turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(halved and peeled). Halve the
@Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into
thirds.

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @Cornflour{10%g} into a #large bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add
the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g} and toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and season with salt and pepper. Stir-fry until just soft,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the onion to the pan with more oil if needed. Stir-fry until the onion has
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then transfer the cooked veg to
another #bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn
every 2-3 mins.

Meanwhile, in another #medium bowl{}, mix together the @Ketjap Manis{50%g},
@Rice Vinegar{30%g}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}.

Once the chicken has browned, add the veg back into the pan and stir-fry for
~{1%minute} more.

Pour the sauce mixture into the pan. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has
reduced slightly and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove from the heat and season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: The sauce should be sticky, but add a splash more water if you'd like.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon into your #bowls{}.

Serve with the sticky chicken and veg on top.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} and spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!